comment: She was a great professor; she helped me understand complicated subjects I was struggling with. She also provides guided notes with information-packed knowledge, which eases my understanding. I highly recommend her for any future classes you take with her.
She was so sweet and kind.  Her lectures were posted on Camren to look back on, and everything tested was on the slides.  There were no tricks in her class.

Dr. Jungers is very kind and the class is very easy with little to no weekly homework. If you like challenging classes, you will be disappointed. Her lectures are pretty boring and she does not add anything more that what you learn in the textbook. Her explanations are also very unclear and her in-class activities are kind of pointless.

She is so sweet and makes her classes interesting and gives breaks when needed! Dropped the 2 lowest quiz grades and let our tests be open note. She offered 4 different extra credit opportunities throughout the semester and also offers extra credit questions on the tests. She definitely wants to see her students succeed and is clear on due dates.
Her class was very easy, the last 2 exams were open note

Great professor Very upbeat, positive, genuine, caring, etc. She gives guided notes, office hours, opportunities to meet tutors, etc She presents the material in a clear and concise way, and you just have to take it in 10/10; Would definitely take one of her classes again.

Dr Jungers is the only reason I didn't drop out this semester. I didn't get to rate my professors on the SEIs because that week was very chaotic, but she deserves a raise. I know you read these, OSU. Get the Kowalskys out, and find more humans like this one. Her classes were fun, informative, and truly made me appreciate M&C. Thank you, Dr Jungers.

Dr. Jungers is a great professor. She tells stories that help you remember information more easily, does kahoots in class, and she gives you guided notes. As always I recommend never missing class if you can help it. The information is important, and it's helpful. She always has a genuine smile on her face and it brightens my day! Take her class!
I would definitely recommend this class and professor. Show up to class, take notes, and you will be solid. Offers extra credit on each quiz and other times too.
Do you Sona studies early, that is the best advice I can give to any student taking intro psych. Dr. Jungers was a great professor, be sure to study, and start studying early!!

She's amazing and very helpful. Class material isn't hard and she makes it very interesting as well. My advice is to read/skim the book and know everything in your notes to be prepared for the quizzes. Do your research credits as soon as possible because it's very easy and do an extra one to boost your grade. Attendance is very important for notes.

Dr. Jungers is an exceptional at what she does. She genuinely cares about her students and their successes. Go to office hours, and she will give you clear guidance to pass the class. There are a few chances for extra credit which will boost your grade along with SONA credit. I am glad I took her class and would take her again in a heartbeat.

Dr. J is the best prof. She's super genuine and obviously cares about her students, as well as psych. Be prepared to take a lot of notes. Show up to class, or you might miss something. She does a lot of review and brings lots of props to make sure you get it. Tests are easy as long as you review your notes! She makes class enjoyable!

Dr. J is THE BEST professor. She's such a genuine person and you can tell she cares about her students, as well as Psych. Be ready to take tons of notes though. She tries her best to make the class seem as interesting as possible by bringing props and allowing discussion. She does a lot if in-class review and tests are super easy.

Loved Jungers! She made everything so clear and easy. If you attend class, you'll understand. We used clickers, she shows movies and provides great examples and activities so the class was very hands on in a way.
She's so nice and very helpful. Just pay attention and you'll do fine.
Very nice, she works with you if you visit office hours. Overall, good experiance.
Jungers is an awesome prof and she's cool too
She is extremely nice and very helpful. She gives a lot of extra credit. This class would be a lot easier if you read the textbook.

She is really nice and sweet. Very interactive with her students, and loves what she teaches. There are a lot papers to write in this class (4), but they aren't too bad. Exams: if you study the study guide your good to go!....a lot of essay Qs.
